    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wooden rods cut to the proposed clear height between finished floors and ceilings of buildings and often marked with subdivisions to aid in the laying out of, for example, door trims, masonry courses, or stair risers.</Note_Text>
